<subSubSection pageId="66" pageNumber="1025" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1058,211,263]" pageId="66" pageNumber="1025">
D i a g n o s i s: This is the only species in the genus. The generic diagnosis will suffice to identify the members of 
<emphasis box="[502,687,241,262]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="1025">Alarius careoritus</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="66" pageNumber="1025" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1059,278,476]" pageId="66" pageNumber="1025">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 5.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[673,753,278,300]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="66" pageNumber="1025" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
. Form: As in 
<figureCitation box="[895,980,278,300]" captionStart="Figs 358-361" captionStartId="117.[151,191,1517,1539]" captionTargetBox="[153,1061,197,1502]" captionTargetId="figure@117.[153,1061,197,1502]" captionTargetPageId="117" captionText="Figs 358-361: Habitus; (358) Alariuscareoritus; (359) Ordinistaxis; (360) Peloniumatrigonatium; (361) Cregyaentrerios." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746842" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746842/files/figure.png" pageId="66" pageNumber="1025">Fig. 358</figureCitation>
. Color: Testaceous. Head: Eyes small, coarsely facetted, eye narrower than frons (EW/FW 15/42); antenna capitate (
<figureCitation box="[421,500,336,359]" captionStart="Figs 43-60" captionStartId="72.[151,191,1361,1383]" captionTargetBox="[157,1053,222,1351]" captionTargetId="figure@72.[152,1057,206,1351]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="Figs 43-60: Antennae; (43) Ordinis taxis; (44) Pelonium tayrona; (45) Neorthopleura turnbowi, male; (46) N. turnbowi, female; (47) Megaphloeus imparilus; (48) Plocamocera catalexis; (48 a) Cregya entrerios; (49) Ridica merida. (50) Kataspinula puebla. (51) Cregya tobagoensis; (52) Topainca patchacutii; (53) Eurycaulis anaxeis; (54) Amboakis expandosa. (55) Ridica achira. (56) Ampleris cacuminis; (57) Sicamus suprus; (58) Sirpa latiflava; (59) Alarius careoritus; (60) Cregya petalosa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746750/files/figure.png" pageId="66" pageNumber="1025">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
), funicular antennomeres filiform, capitular antennomeres 9 and 10 triangular, antennomere 11 ovate. Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[878,966,366,388]" captionStart="Figs 171-178" captionStartId="80.[151,191,1415,1437]" captionTargetBox="[173,1039,201,1402]" captionTargetId="figure@80.[152,1060,201,1403]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="Figs 171-178: Pronota; (171) Akonesis atraordinis; (172) Agnatis curvabilis; (173) Neorthopleura cuspidis; (174) Alarius careoritus; (175) Epiphloeus mantillerii; (176) Cregya vicosa; (177) Cregya arima; (178) Pelonium falcatum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746766" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746766/files/figure.png" pageId="66" pageNumber="1025">Fig. 174</figureCitation>
) slightly transverse, pronotal tubercles well-developed (PW/PL 82/70), disc coarsely punctate and with 4 small tumescences; elytral disc with substriate asetiferous punctures (EL/EW 190/60). Abdomen: Pygidium scutiform.
</paragraph>
