<subSubSection pageId="66" pageNumber="1025" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1058,566,617]" pageId="66" pageNumber="1025">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis box="[544,648,567,588]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="1025">careoritus</emphasis>
, is a Latin name that stems from 
<emphasis box="[1000,1058,567,588]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="1025">careo</emphasis>
(= be without); with regard to the apterous condition of the members of this species.
</paragraph>
